<paragraph id="3340217A40345F1FFCC8FE9B4AEF3906" blockId="35.[826,1442,273,356]" pageId="35" pageNumber="302">
<emphasis id="018BFD6840345F1FFCC8FE9B4CD73944" box="[826,947,273,294]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="302">Etymology:</emphasis>
The name 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF940345F1FFBB2FE9B4BFF3944" authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Hancock &amp; Marcos-García" authorityYear="2007" box="[1088,1179,273,294]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="302" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="conabioi">
<emphasis id="018BFD6840345F1FFBB2FE9B4BFF3944" box="[1088,1179,273,294]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="302">conabioi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is in reference to the Comisión Nacional para el Conocimiento y Uso de la Biodiversidad, which, in 
<collectingCountry id="4BE861EA40345F1FFBFDFEC44B3A3906" box="[1039,1118,334,356]" name="Mexico" pageId="35" pageNumber="302">Mexico</collectingCountry>
, helped fund our fieldwork.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3340217A40345F1FFCC8FEF74A2F3B22" blockId="35.[826,1442,380,832]" pageId="35" pageNumber="302">
<emphasis id="018BFD6840345F1FFCC8FEF74C9939F0" box="[826,1021,381,402]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="302">Taxonomic notes:</emphasis>
The adult of 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF940345F1FFB4BFEF74A5239F3" authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Hancock &amp; Marcos-García" authorityYear="2007" box="[1209,1334,380,402]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="302" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="conabioi">
<emphasis id="018BFD6840345F1FFB4BFEF74A5239F3" box="[1209,1334,380,402]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="302">C. conabioi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is most similar in overall appearance to 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF940345F1FFAF7FE114A3A39D3" authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Hancock &amp; Marcos-García" authorityYear="2007" box="[1285,1374,411,433]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="302" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tapia">
<emphasis id="018BFD6840345F1FFAF7FE114A3A39D3" box="[1285,1374,411,433]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="302">C. tapia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF940345F1FFCC8FE304CCB39AD" authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Hancock &amp; Marcos-García" authorityYear="2007" box="[826,943,442,463]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="302" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albertoi">
<emphasis id="018BFD6840345F1FFCC8FE304CCB39AD" box="[826,943,442,463]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="302">C. albertoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
among the species considered here. It may be distinguished from these species by the ridge at the apex of the scutellum. Among other 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF940345F1FFB17FE7D4C1B3A49" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="302" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undefined-C">
<emphasis id="018BFD6840345F1FFB17FE7D4A0D3A6E" box="[1253,1385,503,524]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="302">Copestylum</emphasis>
species 
<emphasis id="018BFD6840345F1FFC9EFD9C4C1B3A49" box="[876,895,534,555]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="302">C</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="018BFD6840345F1FFC8DFD9C4C8C3A49" box="[895,1000,534,555]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="302">. conabioi</emphasis>
is most similar to 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF940345F1FFB4FFD9C4C8C3A29" authority="(Curran, 1939)" baseAuthorityName="Curran" baseAuthorityYear="1939" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="302" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gertschi">
<emphasis id="018BFD6840345F1FFB4FFD9C4AC63A49" box="[1213,1442,534,555]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="302">Copestylum gertschi</emphasis>
(Curran, 1939)
</taxonomicName>
in general appearance. Both species have a central vitta extending from the antennae to the mouth, lower half of the eyes without hairs, thoracic pile without bristles, and a ridge round the apex of the scutelleum. However, the darker colour of the abdomen and features of the male genitalia separate 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF940345F1FFC83FD674C8A3B63" authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Hancock &amp; Marcos-García" authorityYear="2007" box="[881,1006,748,770]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="302" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="conabioi">
<emphasis id="018BFD6840345F1FFC83FD674C8A3B63" box="[881,1006,748,770]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="302">C. conabioi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from this species. The early stages of 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF940345F1FFCC8FC814CD33B42" authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Hancock &amp; Marcos-García" authorityYear="2007" box="[826,951,779,800]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="302" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="conabioi">
<emphasis id="018BFD6840345F1FFCC8FC814CD33B42" box="[826,951,779,800]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="302">C. conabioi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are easily separated from other bromeliad 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF940345F1FFCC8FCA04CDA3B5D" authorityName="Macquart" authorityYear="1846" box="[826,958,810,831]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="302" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="018BFD6840345F1FFCC8FCA04CDA3B5D" box="[826,958,810,831]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="302">Copestylum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the lack prolegs with crochets.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3340217A40345F1FFCC8FCD24B803BEE" blockId="35.[826,1441,856,908]" pageId="35" pageNumber="302">
